  "tips": [
    "Good stop on the way to the summit. In summer, this is a great place to get lunch and refuel",
    "Going uphill coming around this turn, panoramic views to the southeast open up, with the Dilar ridge in front of the Sierra Nevada.",
    "Sometimes it is already difficult: stop and take a photo or enjoy the wonderful descent to the fullest. Of course, both would be best. But then you would have to cycle up the route again. But I can assure you: During the approximately 30-kilometer descent there is guaranteed to be one or the other opportunity to make a stop to pause for a while - even if only because the brakes have to cool down a bit."
